 🇨🇦 Lac-Supérieur, Québec 
🚗 2h depuis Montréal - 150 km

Deux couchers de soleil, deux ambiances… mais une même paix. 🌅🌿
Un instant au bord du lac Magog, à regarder le ciel s’enflammer, la lumière dorée danser sur l’eau comme un souffle tranquille. Un peu plus tard, perdu dans un champ verdoyant, le soleil se cache doucement derrière la forêt, comme un dernier câlin de la journée.

La nature ne se répète jamais. Elle chuchote différemment selon l’endroit. Mais si tu prends le temps de l’écouter, chaque coucher de soleil te livre un peu de magie.

📸 T’es plus team reflets sur l’eau ou coucher de soleil sur les champs? Dis-le-moi en commentaire 👇

/
/

Two different sunsets. Same kind of peace. 🌅🌿
One moment, I was by the lake, watching the sky turn to fire over Lake Magog — the golden hour dancing on the rippling water, warm and calm like a heartbeat. A few hours later, I found myself in a quiet field, surrounded by green, where the sun tucked itself behind the forest like a gentle goodbye.

Nature doesn’t repeat herself — she whispers differently in every place. But if you’re present enough, you’ll feel the same magic in every sunset.

📸 Which kind of sunset speaks to you more — water reflections or fields of green? Let me know below 👇

latestPosts.caption:
🍦 Found this sweetest spot in Parc Ex —Crèmerie Meetha,  bringing bold Indian flavours to the Montréal ice cream scene! 🇮🇳🍨

@meethamtl isn’t serving your typical vanilla and chocolate — think Parle-G, Bournvita, Haldi Doodh, Elaichi Pista, Mango Rasmalai, Gulab Jamun, Falooda (my fav), and more 🔥

Each scoop is a flavour explosion — rich, layered, nostalgic, and totally unique.

And it doesn’t stop at ice cream — they’ve also got:

☕️ Real chai (hot or iced)
🌹 Falooda 
🥭 Mango lassis
🍦 Soft serve flavours
🧊 Kulfi 

📍 787A Rue de Liège O, Parc-Ex, Montréal

Save this gem & share with your ice cream-loving crew!
